2026-04-30T04:57:17.6788620Z             "body": "## Summary\nImplements a lightweight token-based authentication system with a hierarchical user model and a web UI for token management. Authentication can be disabled entirely via configuration. When enabled, all endpoints require either *** Basic auth credentials.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n- **AuthService** (`src/Ednsv.Core/Services/AuthService.cs`): New service providing:\n  - Root user authentication via configured token hash\n  - Issuance of child tokens with optional delegation rights (`CanIssue`)\n  - Cascade revocation: revoking a user also revokes all tokens they issued (recursively)\n  - Hierarchical permission model: users can only manage their descendants\n  - Persistence to `users.json` with SHA256-based token hashing\n  - Constant-time comparison to prevent timing attacks\n  - Disableable via `\"none\"` marker or empty config\n\n- **Auth Middleware** (`src/Ednsv.Web/Program.cs`): \n  - Runs before static files to protect entire site when enabled\n  - Supports `Authorization: *** and `Authorization: Basic user:token` headers\n  - Returns 401 with WWW-Authenticate challenge on failure\n  - Stores authenticated user in `HttpContext.Items` for endpoint access\n\n- **Auth API Endpoints** (`src/Ednsv.Web/Program.cs`):\n  - `GET /api/auth/me`: Current user info and capabilities\n  - `GET /api/auth/users`: List users visible to caller (descendants for non-root, all for root)\n  - `POST /api/auth/users`: Issue new token (requires `CanIssue` permission)\n  - `POST /api/auth/users/{username}/revoke`: Revoke user and descendants (requires ancestor status)\n\n- **Token Management UI** (`src/Ednsv.Web/wwwroot/tokens.html`):\n  - Dark-themed interface for issuing and revoking tokens\n  - Shows token issuance chain, timestamps, and revocation status\n  - One-time display of newly issued tokens with copy-to-clipboard\n  - Displays current user and permission level\n\n- **Configuration**:\n  - New `DataDir` setting (default `.ednsv-data`) consolidates persistent state\n  - `CacheDir` now lives under `DataDir/cache`\n  - Auth data stored in `DataDir/auth/users.json`\n  - `AuthTokenHash` config setting (overridable by `EDNSV_AUTH_TOKEN_HASH` env var)\n  - New `appsettings.json` with documented defaults\n\n- **Tests** (`tests/Ednsv.Core.Tests/AuthServiceTests.cs`):\n  - 11 test cases covering authentication, issuance, revocation, cascading, persistence, and permission checks\n\n## Notable Implementation Details\n\n- **Token Format**: 32 random bytes base64url-encoded (no padding), hashed with SHA256 before storage\n- **Username Validation**: Alphanumeric plus `.`, `_`, `-`; max 64 characters\n- **Thread Safety**: Lock-protected user list with atomic file writes (write-to-temp, atomic move)\n- **Disableable**: Setting `AuthTokenHash` to `\"none\"` (case-insensitive) or leaving it empty disables auth entirely; service reports `Disabled` and middleware skips authentication\n- **Ancestor Chain**: Revocation and visibility checks walk the issuance chain up to root, with cycle detection (max 1024 hops)\n- **Root User**: Special user `\"ednsv\"` always has `CanIssue=true` and cannot be revoked\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01BJ4t2AqpmWQ4rjDoqLpHkJ",
